tralian open qf  french open r  us open r  team competitions davis cup sf  hopman cup w  last updated on  july  john robert isner born april   is an american professional tennis player considered one of the best servers of the atp world tour isner achieved his careerhigh singles ranking of world no  in april  in  he became the th player to serve more than  aces on the atp world tour he currently has thmost aces in the history of atp having served more than  aces at the  wimbledon championships he played the longest professional tennis match in history defeating nicolas mahut in a total of  hours and  minutes of play over the course of three days he also played the then thlongest singles match a hour minute encounter in the second round of the  french open contents  professional career       reaching the top    first atp title longest match in history   second and third atp titles   reaching the top  and first masters final   sixth seventh atp titles and second masters final   eighth and ninth atp titles   tenth atp title and new highest yearend finish   third masters final and seventh consecutive top finish    longest match in history  playing style and equipment  coaches  personal life  records  significant finals  masters  finals  singles  –  doubles  –  atp career finals  singles   titles  runnersup  doubles   titles  runnersup  team finals  performance timelines  singles  doubles  record against other players  top  wins  references  external links professional careeredit edit john isner at the  us open isner began his professional career in earnest in the summer of  with a world ranking of no  he needed wildcard entries into the main draws of every tournament even at the futures level he won his first tournament of the summer the usa f futures beating the top three seeds along the way then after firstround losses in a challengerlevel and an atplevel tournament he beat five top players and three seeds to win the lexington challenger in july and improve his ranking to no  after just one month at the following weeks tournament at the legg mason tennis classic in washington dc a late withdrawal freed up a wildcard spot which was given to isner at the last minute isner took full advantage of his good fortune recording his first wins over top players he won thirdset tiebreakers on five consecutive days beating no  tim henman no  benjamin becker no  qualifier wayne odesnik no  tommy haas and no  gaël monfils to reach the final where he fell to fellow american andy roddick his week raised his ranking to no  in the world after six weeks on the pro tour isners washington success earned him wildcard entries into three more atp tournaments the masters series event in cincinnati a week later new haven and the us open he lost in the first round in cincinnati to quarterfinalist no  david ferrer the following week in new haven he beat no  becker a second time before falling to ferrer for the second week in a row in his us open début he defeated the thseeded player former quarterfinalist jarkko nieminen firing  aces along the way he proceeded to win his secondround match against rik de voest before losing in the third round to top seed and eventual champion roger federer isner was one of only two players to take a set from federer in the championship his us open performance improved his ranking to no  after the us open isner continued to play exclusively in north america and finished the year ranked no  that year isner was added to the united states davis cup team as a practice partner edit isners no  ranking in november  was just good enough to get him direct entry into his first australian open after several players ranked above him dropped out he was defeated in the first round of the  australian open by veteran fabrice santoro of france teamed with croat ivo karlović  cm  in taller than isner karlović is currently the tallest player on the atp tour isner also lost in the first round of doubles isner broke into the top  at no  in february with a quarterfinal appearance at the atp event in san jose beating no  florent serra and no  tommy haas he maintained a top ranking in the first three months of the year beating six players in the top  while playing exclusively in atplevel events isner played in his first french open and wimbledon losing in the first round of each he also played in the us open where he lost in the first round he ended the year ranked no  in the world  reaching the top edit isner qualified for the singles draw of the  heineken open in auckland after winning three consecutive threeset matches in qualifying his final match saw him bounce back from a – deficit in the third set to eventually beat brazilian thomaz bellucci in a tiebreaker in the main draw isner beat albert montañés and countryman robby ginepri before ultimately exiting with a loss in the quarterfinals isner received a wildcard entry into the  australian open after winning the united states tennis associations wildcard tournament beating donald young and jesse levine along the way despite serving  aces against his firstround opponent slovakias dominik hrbatý he lost in four sets isner began working with a new coach craig boynton who had coached former world no  jim courier in the s in march  at the  indian wells tournament isner pulled off a major upset by defeating ninth seed gaël monfils this was isners first win over a top player after four previous defeats he then went on to defeat former world no  marat safin before losing to world no  juan martín del potro in the fourth round in april  at the us mens clay court championships in houston texas at river oaks country club isner made it as far as the quarterfinals where he was defeated by fellow american wayne odesnik isner qualified for the french open but had to withdraw after being diagnosed with mononucleosis which caused him to miss wimbledon as well in august  he defeated world no  jowilfried tsonga and world no  tomáš berdych en route to the semifinals of the atp world tour  event in washington before losing to world no  andy roddick this performance brought him to a careerhigh ranking of no  and a special exemption into the masters  series event in montreal where he defeated jesse levine before losing to mikhail youzhny he earned a wildcard into the masters  series event in cincinnati where he defeated world no  tommy haas before losing to world no  jérémy chardy in the second round isners forehand return to verdasco at the  us open unseeded and ranked no  in the world entering the us open isner defeated world no  victor hănescu in the first round which was his first win in a grand slam tournament since the  us open ending a streak of six consecutive defeats he then advanced to the third round where he defeated world no  and fellow american andy roddick in five sets for his first victory over roddick his first victory in a fiveset match and the first time he advanced past the third round of a grand slam tournament he was then defeated in the fourth round by world no  fernando verdasco in four sets his us open performance brought his ranking to a careerhigh no  after playing in vienna basel and the paris masters isner finished the year at a careerhigh no  in the world he has credited his work with boynton for helping him get back on track following his disappointing  season his progress was acknowledged by his peers as he was voted the atp most improved player for  becoming the tenth american to win the award and the first since andre agassi in   first atp title longest match in historyedit isner hits a forehand isner began the year at the  heineken open in auckland unseeded he reached his second career atp final and first since washington in  in the final he saved a championship point to defeat  australian open finalist arnaud clément the victory in auckland was isners first atp tour title after the victory he donated  of his winnings to aid rescue action for the  haiti earthquake the victory catapulted isner into the to