ted on  july  john robert isner born april   is an american professional tennis player considered one of the best servers of the atp world tour isner achieved his careerhigh singles ranking of world no  in april  in  he became the th player to serve more than  aces on the atp world tour he currently has thmost aces in the history of atp having served more than  aces at the  wimbledon championships he played the longest professional tennis match in history defeating nicolas mahut in a total of  hours and  minutes of play over the course of three days he also played the then thlongest singles match a hour minute encounter in the second round of the  french open contents  professional career       reaching the top    first atp title longest match in history   second and third atp titles   reaching the top  and first masters final   sixth seventh atp titles and second masters final   eighth and ninth atp titles   tenth atp title and new highest yearend finish   third masters final and seventh consecutive top finish    longest match in history  playing style and equipment  coaches  personal life  records  significant finals  masters  finals  singles  –  doubles  –  atp career finals  singles   titles  runnersup  doubles   titles  runnersup  team finals  performance timelines  singles  doubles  record against other players  top  wins  references  external links professional careeredit edit john isner at the  us open isner began his professional career in earnest in the summer of  with a world ranking of no  he needed wildcard entries into the main draws of every tournament even at the futures level he won his first tournament of the summer the usa f futures beating the top three seeds along the way then after firstround losses in a challengerlevel and an atplevel tournament he beat five top players and three seeds to win the lexington challenger in july and improve his ranking to no  after just one month at the following weeks tournament at the legg mason tennis classic in washington dc a late withdrawal freed up a wildcard spot which was given to isner at the last minute isner took full advantage of his good fortune recording his first wins over top players he won thirdset tiebreakers on five consecutive days beating no  tim henman no  benjamin becker no  qualifier wayne odesnik no  tommy haas and no  gaël monfils to reach the final where he fell to fellow american andy roddick his week raised his ranking to no  in the world after six weeks on the pro tour isners washington success earned him wildcard entries into three more atp tournaments the masters series event in cincinnati a week later new haven and the us open he lost in the first round in cincinnati to quarterfinalist no  david ferrer the following week in new haven he beat no  becker a second time before falling to ferrer for the second week in a row in his us open début he defeated the thseeded player former quarterfinalist jarkko nieminen firing  aces along the way he proceeded to win his secondround match against rik de voest before losing in the third round to top seed and eventual champion roger federer isner was one of only two players to take a set from federer in the championship his us open performance improved his ranking to no  after the us open isner continued to play exclusively in north america and finished the year ranked no  that year isner was added to the united states davis cup team as a practice partner edit isners no  ranking in november  was just good enough to get him direct entry into his first australian open after several players ranked above him dropped out he was defeated in the first round of the  australian open by veteran fabrice santoro of france teamed with croat ivo karlović  cm  in taller than isner karlović is currently the tallest player on the atp tour isner also lost in the first round of doubles isner broke into the top  at no  in february with a quarterfinal appearance at the atp event in san jose beating no  florent serra and no  tommy haas he maintained a top ranking in the first three months of the year beating six players in the top  while playing exclusively in atplevel events isner played in his first french open and wimbledon losing in the first round of each he also played in the us open where he lost in the first round he ended the year ranked no  in the world  reaching the top edit isner qualified for the singles draw of the  heineken open in auckland after winning three consecutive threeset matches in qualifying his final match saw him bounce back from a – deficit in the third set to eventually beat brazilian thomaz bellucci in a tiebreaker in the main draw isner beat albert montañés and countryman robby ginepri before ultimately exiting with a loss in the quarterfinals isner received a wildcard entry into the  australian open after winning the united states tennis associations wildcard tournament beating donald young and jesse levine along the way despite serving  aces against his firstround opponent slovakias dominik hrbatý he lost in four sets isner began working with a new coach craig boynton who had coached former world no  jim courier in the s in march  at the  indian wells tournament isner pulled off a major upset by defeating ninth seed gaël monfils this was isners first win over a top player after four previous defeats he then went on to defeat former world no  marat safin before losing to world no  juan martín del potro in the fourth round in april  at the us mens clay court championships in houston texas at river oaks country club isner made it as far as the quarterfinals where he was defeated by fellow american wayne odesnik isner qualified for the french open but had to withdraw after being diagnosed with mononucleosis which caused him to miss wimbledon as well in august  he defeated world no  jowilfried tsonga and world no  tomáš berdych en route to the semifinals of the atp world tour  event in washington before losing to world no  andy roddick this performance brought him to a careerhigh ranking of no  and a special exemption into the masters  series event in montreal where he defeated jesse levine before losing to mikhail youzhny he earned a wildcard into the masters  series event in cincinnati where he defeated world no  tommy haas before losing to world no  jérémy chardy in the second round isners forehand return to verdasco at the  us open unseeded and ranked no  in the world entering the us open isner defeated world no  victor hănescu in the first round which was his first win in a grand slam tournament since the  us open ending a streak of six consecutive defeats he then advanced to the third round where he defeated world no  and fellow american andy roddick in five sets for his first victory over roddick his first victory in a fiveset match and the first time he advanced past the third round of a grand slam tournament he was then defeated in the fourth round by world no  fernando verdasco in four sets his us open performance brought his ranking to a careerhigh no  after playing in vienna basel and the paris masters isner finished the year at a careerhigh no  in the world he has credited his work with boynton for helping him get back on track following his disappointing  season his progress was acknowledged by his peers as he was voted the atp most improved player for  becoming the tenth american to win the award and the first since andre agassi in   first atp title longest match in historyedit isner hits a forehand isner began the year at the  heineken open in auckland unseeded he reached his second career atp final and first since washington in  in the final he saved a championship point to defeat  australian open finalist arnaud clément the victory in auckland was isners first atp tour title after the victory he donated  of his winnings to aid rescue action for the  haiti earthquake the victory catapulted isner into the top  for the first time and also allowed him to surpass sam querrey to become the second highestranked american for the first time behind only andy roddick isner said he intended to finish the year in the top  and given his ascendency in the world rankings combined with the absence of roddick and james blake for the  davis cup season it became increasingly likely that isner would qualify to play singles for the us davis cup team for the first time in his career after gilles simon withdrew isner became the final seed for the  australian open in the first round he defeated world no  andreas seppi for his first victory at the australian open and his first victory at a grand slam other than the us open he then advanced to the round of  before losing to world no  and eventual finalist andy murray after the australian open davis cup captain patrick mcenroe announced that isner and querrey would be first and second singles on the  united states davis cup team for the teams  davis cup world group firstround match in serbia on indoor clay in march  isner described the selection as a dream come true isner next entered the  regions morgan keegan championships in memphis seeded sixth he made it to the finals before losing to sam querrey in the doubles event isner teamed up with querrey to win the tournament defeating britishaustralian pair of ross hutchins and jordan kerr prior to the davis cup tie isner competed at the  abierto mexicano telcel championships an atp world tour  series event on clay where he was the fifth seed he lost in the first round to simon greul despite the loss isner following the tournament moved into the top  for the first time isner appeared at the  davis cup first round where usa was up against serbia in his two singles matches he faced serbias team of world no  novak djokovic and world no  viktor troicki he lost the first singles match against viktor troicki but bounced back by winning the doubles match with bob bryan as a replacement for foodpoisoned mike bryan in his second singles match he lost to novak djokovic which enabled serbia to defeat the united states at the  bnp paribas open masters  in indian wells he was seeded th and advanced to the fourth round before losing to world no  and defending champion rafael nadal afterwards he appeared in the second master series tournament of the season the  sony ericsson open masters  in miami as the th seed he advanced to the third round before losing to th seed juan carlos ferrero isner began the claycourt season with an openinground loss to world no  xavier malisse at the us mens claycourt championship followed by a round of  showing at his firstever rome masters where he defeated horacio zeballos before losing to thomaz bellucci however he teamed with querrey to reach the doubles final in rome before losing to bob and mike bryan his doubles performance raised his doubles ranking to the top  for the first time his next tournament was the  serbian open where he was the second seed behind defending champion tournament host and world no  djokovic isner advanced to the first claycourt final of his career third final of the year and fourth final of his career in the final he lost to querrey despite having a match point this was the second consecutive final isner lost to querrey after serving for the championship however isners finals performance improved his ranking to a careerhigh no  isners next tournament was his debut appearance at the madrid masters seeded thirteenth he advanced to the round of  before losing to world no  and eventual champion nadal isner then played in the  french open his ranking assured his first direct seed into a grand slam event seeded th he defeated andrey golubev in the first round for his first singles victory at the french open he advanced to the third round before losing to no  seed and eventual semifinalist tomáš berdych in doubles he and querrey were the th seeds but withdrew prior to the start of the tournament after querreys firstround loss in singles despite being ranked no  in the world entering the wimbledon isner was seeded th by the tournament committee due to his lack of experience on grass but was moved up to rd following the withdrawal of radek štěpánek in the first round isner played nicolas mahut in the longest match in tennis history prevailing – – – – – however fatigued and having little time to recover his energy isner was beaten by thiemo de bakker in the second round – – – having served no aces he also pulled out of the doubles where he and querrey had been th seeds despite having been eliminated in the second round isners total of  aces were more than any other player throughout the championship his wimbledon performance brought his ranking to a careerhigh no  in the world isners next tournament was the  atlanta tennis championships where he played doubles with james blake and reached the semifinals in singles isner was second seed and made it to his fourth final of the year before losing to mardy fish which dropped his career record in finals to – – against americans isner next competed at the legg mason tennis classic the atp world tour  series event in washington dc and site of his breakthrough performance in  isner was also to compete in the doubles with sam querrey but withdrew due to shoulder concerns seeded fifth in singles isner made it to the round of  before losing to xavier malisse isner next played in the cincinnati masters where he was unseeded after defeating łukasz kubot in the first round he faced  wimbledon finalist and  tennis masters cup champion david nalbandian but was forced to retire up a break at – in the first set after injuring his right ankle although isner was found to have suffered ligament damage to the ankle he chose not to withdraw from the us open singles tournament at the  us open isner was th seed and defeated frederico gil in the first round after the match he revealed that although the initial diagnosis was a right ankle ligament tear a second opinion revealed that the damage was a strain and not a tear and he declared his ankle  healed he then advanced to the third round before losing to th seed and  us open semifinalist mikhail youzhny the loss dropped isner out of the top  and from the no  to the no  ranked american player due to his ankle injury he chose not to compete in doubles following the us open isner participated with mardy fish and sam querrey in the davis cup tie against colombia winning the doubles match with fish as his partner the us won the match – to remain in the  davis cup world group isner was next granted a wildcard to participate in the  china open his first time competing in beijing in doubles he teamed with querrey losing in the first round to bob and mike bryan in singles isner was unseeded but made it to the semifinals before losing to world no  and defending champion novak djokovic isner next competed in the shanghai masters where he was unseeded and made it to the second round before losing to world no  and reigning australian open champion roger federer in their first meeting since the  us open  second and third atp titlesedit isner began the year by teaming with bethanie matteksands to win the mixed doubles hopman cup final for the us defeating belgiums justine henin and ruben bemelmans following his win in perth isner returned to auckland to defend his atp title at the  heineken open after a bye in his first round the third seed faced dutch world no  robin haase isner defeated haase to go through to the quarterfinals where he was defeated by david nalbandian in straight sets isner next played in the  australian open he entered the tournament seeded th and received a tough draw including radek štěpánek marin čilić and rafael nadal isner came up against french world no  florent serra whom he easily defeated isner faced radek štěpánek in the second round after losing the first set isner rallied to defeat stepanek to progress into the third round in the third round isner faced fellow top player marin čilić the match went to five sets with cilic emerging as the eventual winner at the  french open isner was drawn against top seed and defending champion rafael nadal isner took a twosetstoone lead against nadal who had never played a fiveset match at roland garros before nadal went on to win the title in the  wimbledon mens singles draw isner was paired against mahut in the first round a rematch of the worlds longest match from the previous years tournament isner won in straight sets however he lost in the second round to the th seed nicolás almagro in four sets dropping his  record to – isner next took a lastminute wild card to participate in the  hall of fame tennis championships replacing compatriot and defending champion mardy fish who was chosen to play in the davis cup for the united states during that weekend isner was the top seed and defeated karol beck  australian open finalist arnaud clément alex bogomolov jr and tobias kamke without dropping a set to reach his first career grasscourt final in the final he defeated olivier rochus to become the first top seed in  years to win the event the title was his first of  and second of his career and ended a threematch losing streak in finals the championship raised isners world ranking from no  to no  isner next played in the  atlanta tennis championships where he was the third seed he defeated james blake lu yenhsun and gilles müller to reach his second consecutive tour final in the final he faced mardy fish in a rematch of the  final isner was ultimately defeated by fish he then reached the semifinals of the legg mason tennis classic defeating tobias kamke james blake victor troicki before losing to gaël monfils at the rogers cup isner defeated marcos baghdatis but lost to viktor troicki in the second round isner won the winstonsalem open as the fourth seed defeating dudi sela jarkko nieminen marcos baghdatis and andy roddick in the semifinals before defeating julien benneteau in the final isner in us open  in the  us open isner defeated marcos baghdatis robby ginepri alex bogomolov jr and gilles simon on the way to his first grand slam quarterfinal there he was defeated by andy murray isner reached the semifinals at the masters  in paris where he held three match points before losing to jowilfried tsonga in the semifinals the result brought him back into the world top  he finished the year ranked no  his second consecutive yearend top  ranking and his highest yearend ranking to date  reaching the top  and first masters finaledit isner serving in his olympic mens singles quarterfinal match against roger federer isner defeated david nalbandian in the second round of the  australian open in a fiveset match but was defeated in the third round by feliciano lópez he beat world no  roger federer in switzerland in the davis cup first round as well as beating marco chiudinelli in another singles rubber to help propel the us team to victory over the swiss he then reached the final of the indian wells masters by beating world no  novak djokovic in three sets in the semifinals before being defeated by federer in straight sets in the final isner also reached the doubles final of the same tournament partnering sam querrey in the us davis cup quarterfinals against france isner defeated gilles simon in the first live rubber of the tie in straight sets two days later isner clinched the tie and propelled the united states into the semifinals by defeating french no  jowilfried tsonga in four sets a week before roland garros he was top seed in nice but was upset by nikolay davydenko in the quarterfinals in the  french open he defeated rogério dutra da silva in the first round before being defeated by wildcard paulhenri mathieu in the second round – – – – – in the secondlongest ever roland garros match at  hours and  minutes in the wimbledon championships he was the eleventh seed however he was upset by rd ranked alejandro falla in five sets being eliminated in the first round if he had won this match he would have gone on to face mahut for the third straight year he beat mahut at the hall of fame tennis championships in july on his way to winning the championship for the second consecutive year isner reached the semifinals at the  atlanta tennis championships losing to andy roddick isner defeated milos raonic in the rogers cup atp  quarterfinals and played richard gasquet for a place in the final but lost isner was chosen to be on special london  coke cans isner lost in the quarterfinals of the olympics to the runnerup roger federer in the mens doubles event he and andy roddick did not progress beyond the first round isner won his second title of the year at the  winstonsalem open defeating tomáš berdych in the final it was the second consecutive year that he won the title at winstonsalem at the us open he lost in the third round to philipp kohlschreiber  sixth seventh atp titles and second masters finaledit isner serving at the  us open isner was seeded first in sydney but he lost in the second round to ryan harrison in straight sets he did not appear at the  australian open the following week because of a bone bruise in his right knee isner won his sixth atp title and first on clay defeating nicolás almagro in the us clay court championships final in houston at the monte carlo masters he was eliminated in the first round he also made early exits in madrid and rome at the french open isner recovered from two sets down in his firstround match to beat ryan harrison in five sets the next day isner once again recovered from two sets down to level the match this time against tommy haas saving a record  match points in the fourth set however isner then let a lead slip and failed to convert a match point of his own and haas eventually won the fifth set at the  topshelf open in shertogenbosch isner went out in the first round defeated by young russian evgeny donskoy at wimbledon isner was injured and had to retire during his secondround match against frenchman adrian mannarino after avenging himself on donskoy in the first round in july isner won his second title of the year and his first in atlanta after appearing twice before in the final he defeated kevin anderson in the final in a threetiebreak match which was billed as the tallest final in atp history their combined heights adding up to  feet  inches in washington he reached the final and lost to juan martín del potro after winning the first set at the  rogers cup in montréal isner lost in the first round to the canadian no  vasek pospisil who went on to reach the semifinals he won the first set but then lost two tiebreaks during a busy summer he reached another final in cincinnati beating richard gasquet and then three top players in a row first milos raonic then novak djokovic then juan martín del potro in the semifinals for the first time he lost to rafael nadal in his second masters  final and subsequently pulled out of the winstonsalem tournament in the us open he beat gaël monfils in the second round but lost for the second consecutive year to philipp kohlschreiber in the third round  eighth and ninth atp titlesedit isner started his season at the  hopman cup with countrywoman sloane stephens beginning strong with a win over spain however the pair then lost their next two ties against france and the czech republic respectively one week later he won the  heineken open defeating lu yenhsun in the final in two tiebreak sets at the  australian open he faced martin kližan in the first round but after losing the first two sets he ultimately retired due to an ankle injury isner then reached the semifinals of the delray beach international tennis championships losing to eventual champion marin čilić in straight sets at the  indian wells masters isner received a bye into round two after which he defeated nikolay davydenko lu yenhsun fernando verdasco and ernests gulbis en route to the semifinals where he would face novak djokovic in a rematch of their  semifinal however this time isner lost in three sets the semifinal run in indian wells did however secure him a return to the top  at the miami masters isner again received a bye into round two where he faced and beat countryman donald young he then defeated nicolás almagro in the third round only to lose to tomáš berdych in the fourth round in houston he was defending a title but lost his first match in the second round to dustin brown with the points he lost he slipped out of the top ten to a ranking of no  in madrid he teamed up with tomáš berdych in the doubles draw in singles he made it to the third round where he lost to david ferrer he went down in the first round at the rome masters  in nice the week before the french open he made it to the quarterfinals where he was defeated by argentine federico delbonis at roland garros he reached the fourth round where he went down to berdych he did not play a grass tuneup tournament before wimbledon isner after his second round match at wimbledon  at the  wimbledon championships isner reached the third round where he lost to feliciano lópez in four sets with three tiebreaks in newport rhode island john made it to the quarterfinals where he lost to jack sock however he got revenge in the semifinals in atlanta a couple of weeks later and went on to win the tournament his ninth with a win over dudi sela at the us open isner reached the third round where he lost to philipp kohlschreiber for the third consecutive year isner hired justin gimelstob as his new coach at the end of the  season  tenth atp title and new highest yearend finishedit isner started the season slowly making the third round of the australian open and having only a quarterfinal showing in memphis before making it into the semifinals in miami with three wins in a row defeating dimitrov raonic and nishikori he lost to djokovic in the semifinals he lost to djokovic again in straight sets in indian wells in the third round after winning qualifier jürgen melzer in the second round in monte carlo he lost to rafael nadal in the third round he made the quarterfinals in madrid where he lost to tomáš berdych in nice he made the semifinals losing to dominic thiem isner during practice at the queens club aegon championships in london england at roland garros he lost to jérémy chardy in the second round on grass he made the quarterfinals at queens club and the third round at wimbledon to marin cilic in his thirdround match at wimbledon in this match isner played another marathon eventually losing to the thenworld no  by  in the fifth set after two days of play isner lost in the first round in newport to eventual champion rajeev ram he successfully defended his title in atlanta in july to win his th tour title and third in a row in the tournament defeating marcos baghdatis in the final in straight sets the following week he reached the final of the  tournament in washington dc losing in the final to kei nishikori he also reached the quarterfinals of the rogers cup in montréal losing in three tiebeaks to jérémy chardy however the next week in cincinnati he went out in the first round against sam querrey he skipped winstonsalem his home tournament the week before the us open at the us open isner advanced to the fourth round losing to federer in straight sets but nonetheless marked his best grand slam result of the year he reached the third round in shanghai before losing to andy murray in three sets and made his third quarterfinal masters appearance of the year in paris after beating federer in three sets isner finished the year at his best yearend ranking to date at world no   third masters final and seventh consecutive top finishedit isner started his season in auckland and reached the quarterfinals losing to eventual champion roberto bautista agut at australian open he reached the fourth round for the first time since  defeating spaniards marcel granollers and feliciano lópez before losing in straights sets to david ferrer instead of playing the us spring hardcourt tournaments isner decided to play two clay court tournaments in south america losing his first match in both to dusan lajovic in argentina and guido pella in brazil in the first round of davis cup isner defeated bernard tomic and sam groth to help upset australia  and move the united states into the quarterfinals against croatia isner reached the fourth round at bnp paribas open for the third year in a row before losing to kei nishikori and he was then upset early in miami open by tim smyczek despite missing most of the clay season only playing us mens clay court championships and geneva open isner reached the fourth round of the french open for only the second time in his career losing to eventual finalist andy murray in straight sets isners season continued with early losses in both grass tournaments he played losing to gilles müller at aegon championships and losing a marathon match to jowilfried tsonga at wimbledon isner started the us open series with a disappointing loss in the second round of the rogers cup to ryan harrison isner rebounded by reaching his first final of the season and his fourth consecutive final at the atlanta open losing in straight sets to nick kyrgios isner skipped the summer olympics due to a lack of ranking points and prize money electing to focus on the summer hardcourt tournaments of the us open series after isner lost in straight sets in the second round to milos raonic and steve johnson reached the quarterfinals in cincinnati isner lost the title of the topranked american man for the first time in three years although he regained it in the following week johnson took it back over following the us open after isner was unable to defend his fourth round points losing in the third round to kyle edmund in four sets isner teamed up with jack sock to win his second masters doubles title and fourth overall doubles title at the shanghai masters unseeded at the final regular tournament of the season isner would prevail against seeded players david ferrer and marin cilic to reach his third masters final and second final of the season at the paris masters his semifinal victory allowed isner to again finish the year as the no  american for the fifth consecutive year and inside the top  for the seventh consecutive season in the final isner lost to the newly crowned world number  andy murray thus leaving him titleless in singles for the first time since  edit isner reached quarterfinals in auckland memphis and houston he reached the semifinals in rome at the italian open where he was defeated by eventual champion alexander zverev at the french open isner came off to a strong start beating jordan thompson and paolo lorenzi in the first and second rounds respectively however he fell in the third round to karen khachanov in  sets isner competed at the  wimbledon championships where he defeated qualifier taylor fritz in the first round before losing to dudi sela in  sets the following match at the dell technologies hall of fame open in newport isner defeated qualifier matthew ebden   in the final to win his first singles title of the year longest match in historyedit main article isner–mahut match at the  wimbledon championships at the  wimbledon championships isner ranked  faced qualifier nicolas mahut in the first round isner won the match – – – – – the final set alone was longer than the previous longest match in the match isner set the record for most aces in a match breaking ivo karlovićs record of  mahut passed the old mark as well isner set a new record of  aces ahead of the  aces served by mahut the first four sets were played on june  at  bst on june  the match was suspended due to darkness for a second day at – in the fifth set the match resumed on june  at  bst starting the third day of the match overall the match lasted eleven hours and five minutes isner also set the record for most games won in a wimbledon match with  the match brought isner a measure of fame particularly in the united states he had guest appearances on good morning america and the late show with david letterman and threw the ceremonial first pitch at a new york yankees game in yankee stadium he and mahut also won the  espy award for best recordbreaking performance in sport line score           john isner       nicolas mahut q      playing style and equipmentedit isner has an extremely powerful and consistent serve thanks in part to his ft in height which makes him the third tallest player on tour behind ivo karlović and reilly opelka commentatorswho have also praised his composure in five consecutive thirdset tiebreaker wins in washington he delivered huge serves when it mattered most isner also has a very powerful forehand which he uses in tandem with his serve isner will often go for onetwo points a big serve followed up by a big forehand he is also known to back up his serves with approaches to the net though he does not strictly serveandvolley isners movement around the court is hampered by his body and he is hurt by players that move him around the court isners fitness has improved considerably throughout the years as he displayed during his win in the longest tennis match ever at wimbledon against nicolas mahut as of january  isner is sponsored by lacoste and prince for his attire and rackets respectively his attire carried through most of  he switched his attire to fila in  at the australian open coachesedit isners first coach was craig boynton who worked with him from  to  and helped develop his style of play isner and boynton split over reportedly mutual agreement isner then hired mike sell who helped him to significant success such as defeating roger federer david nalbandian and novak djokovic during his time with sell isners ranking stayed around no in the world after parting from sell in  isner teamed with justin gimelstob and worked with him until april  with gimelstob isners ranking stayed around  until  where he dropped to  personal lifeedit isner started playing tennis seriously at age  he played competitively for westside swim and tennis club in greensboro north carolina throughout his childhood he is a graduate of walter hines page senior high school in greensboro and the university of georgia where he majored in speech communication he currently resides in tampa florida where he trains at the saddlebrook academy alongside other american tennis pros such as james blake and mardy fish isner is a supporter of the fremantle football club in the australian football league and the carolina panthers of the national football league recordsedit these records were attained in the open era of tennis tournament year record accomplished player tied wimbledon   aces in an atp singles match stands alone  aces in a grand slam singles match stands alone  aces in a single set stands alone  games won in a single match stands alone  games lost in a single match that he won stands alone  winners in a single match stands alone longest singles match ever played  hours  minutes nicolas mahut longest play in a single day  hours  minutes nicolas mahut  games in a single day nicolas mahut hall of fame championships  won an atp tournament never facing a break point tommy haas other records   career record in tiebreaks significant finalsedit masters  finalsedit singles  –edit outcome year championship surface opponent score runnerup  indian wells hard roger federer –– – runnerup  cincinnati hard rafael nadal –– –– runnerup  paris masters hard i andy murray – –– – doubles  –edit outcome year championship surface partner opponents score runnerup  rome clay sam querrey bob bryan mike bryan – – winner  rome clay sam querrey mardy fish andy roddick wo runnerup  indian wells hard sam querrey rafael nadal marc lópez – –– winner  shanghai hard jack sock henri kontinen john peers – – atp career finalsedit singles   titles  runnersupedit legend grand slam tournaments – atp world tour finals – atp world tour masters  – atp world tour  series – atp world tour  series – titles by surface hard – clay – grass – carpet – titles