one of the best servers of the atp world tour isner achieved his careerhigh singles ranking of world no  in april  in  he became the th player to serve more than  aces on the atp world tour he currently has thmost aces in the history of atp having served more than  aces at the  wimbledon championships he played the longest professional tennis match in history defeating nicolas mahut in a total of  hours and  minutes of play over the course of three days he also played the then thlongest singles match a hour minute encounter in the second round of the  french open contents  professional career       reaching the top    first atp title longest match in history   second and third atp titles   reaching the top  and first masters final   sixth seventh atp titles and second masters final   eighth and ninth atp titles   tenth atp title and new highest yearend finish   third masters final and seventh consecutive top finish    longest match in history  playing style and equipment  coaches  personal life  records  significant finals  masters  finals  singles  –  doubles  –  atp career finals  singles   titles  runnersup  doubles   titles  runnersup  team finals  performance timelines  singles  doubles  record against other players  top  wins  references  external links professional careeredit edit john isner at the  us open isner began his professional career in earnest in the summer of  with a world ranking of no  he needed wildcard entries into the main draws of every tournament even at the futures level he won his first tournament of the summer the usa f futures beating the top three seeds along the way then after firstround losses in a challengerlevel and an atplevel tournament he beat five top players and three seeds to win the lexington challenger in july and improve his ranking to no  after just one month at the following weeks tournament at the legg mason tennis classic in washington dc a late withdrawal freed up a wildcard spot which was given to isner at the last minute isner took full advantage of his good fortune recording his first wins over top players he won thirdset tiebreakers on five consecutive days beating no  tim henman no  benjamin becker no  qualifier wayne odesnik no  tommy haas and no  gaël monfils to reach the final where he fell to fellow american andy roddick his week raised his ranking to no  in the world after six weeks on the pro tour isners washington success earned him wildcard entries into three more atp tournaments the masters series event in cincinnati a week later new haven and the us open he lost in the first round in cincinnati to quarterfinalist no  david ferrer the following week in new haven he beat no  becker a second time before falling to ferrer for the second week in a row in his us open début he defeated the thseeded player former quarterfinalist jarkko nieminen firing  aces along the way he proceeded to win his secondround match against rik de voest before losing in the third round to top seed and eventual champion roger federer isner was one of only two players to take a set from federer in the championship his us open performance improved his ranking to no  after the us open isner continued to play exclusively in north america and finished the year ranked no  that year isner was added to the united states davis cup team as a practice partner edit isners no  ranking in november  was just good enough to get him direct entry into his first australian open after several players ranked above him dropped out he was defeated in the first round of the  australian open by veteran fabrice santoro of france teamed with croat ivo karlović  cm  in taller than isner karlović is currently the tallest player on the atp tour isner also lost in the first round of doubles isner broke into the top  at no  in february with a quarterfinal appearance at the atp event in san jose beating no  florent serra and no  tommy haas he maintained a top ranking in the first three months of the year beating six players in the top  while playing exclusively in atplevel events isner played in his first french open and wimbledon losing in the first round of each he also played in the us open where he lost in the first round he ended the year ranked no  in the world  reaching the top edit isner qualified for the singles draw of the  heineken open in auckland after winning three consecutive threeset matches in qualifying his final match saw him bounce back from a – deficit in the third set to eventually beat brazilian thomaz bellucci in a tiebreaker in the main draw isner beat albert montañés and countryman robby ginepri before ultimately exiting with a loss in the quarterfinals isner received a wildcard entry into the  australian open after winning the united states tennis associations wildcard tournament beating donald young and jesse levine along the way despite serving  aces against his firstround opponent slovakias dominik hrbatý he lost in four sets isner began working with a new coach craig boynton who had coached former world no  jim courier in the s in march  at the  indian wells tournament isner pulled off a major upset by defeating ninth seed gaël monfils this was isners first win over a top player after four previous defeats he then went on to defeat former world no  marat safin before losing to world no  juan martín del potro in the fourth round in april  at the us mens clay court championships in houston texas at river oaks country club isner made it as far as the quarterfinals where he was defeated by fellow american wayne odesnik isner qualified for the french open but had to withdraw after being diagnosed with mononucleosis which caused him to miss wimbledon as well in august  he defeated world no  jowilfried tsonga and world no  tomáš berdych en route to the semifinals of the atp world tour  event in washington before losing to world no  andy roddick this performance brought him to a careerhigh ranking of no  and a special exemption into the masters  series event in montreal where he defeated jesse levine before losing to mikhail youzhny he earned a wildcard into the masters  series event in cincinnati where he defeated world no  tommy haas before losing to world no  jérémy chardy in the second round isners forehand return to verdasco at the  us open unseeded and ranked no  in the world entering the us open isner defeated world no  victor hănescu in the first round which was his first win in a grand slam tournament since the  us open ending a streak of six consecutive defeats he then advanced to the third round where he defeated world no  and fellow american andy roddick in five sets for his first victory over roddick his first victory in a fiveset match and the first time he advanced past the third round of a grand slam tournament he was then defeated in the fourth round by world no  fernando verdasco in four sets his us open performance brought his ranking to a careerhigh no  after playing in vienna basel and the paris masters isner finished the year at a careerhigh no  in the world he has credited his work with boynton for helping him get back on track following his disappointing  season his progress was acknowledged by his peers as he was voted the atp most improved player for  becoming the tenth american to win the award and the first since andre agassi in   first atp title longest match in historyedit isner hits a forehand isner began the year at the  heineken open in auckland unseeded he reached his second career atp final and first since washington in  in the final he saved a championship point to defeat  australian open finalist arnaud clément the victory in auckland was isners first atp tour title after the victory he donated  of his winnings to aid rescue action for the  haiti earthquake the victory catapulted isner into the top  for the first time and also allowed him to surpass sam querrey to become the second highestranked american for the first time behind only andy roddick isner said he intended to finish the year in the top  and given his ascendency in the world rankings combined with the absence of roddick and james blake for the  davis cup season it became increasingly likely that isner would qualify to play singles for the us davis cup team for the first time in his career after gilles simon withdrew isner became the final seed for the  australian open in the first round he defeated world no  andreas seppi for his first victory at the australian open and his first victory at a grand slam other than the us open he then advanced to the round of  before losing to world no  and eventual finalist andy murray after the australian open davis cup captain patrick mcenroe announced that isner and querrey would be first and second singles on the  united states davis cup team for the teams  davis cup world group firstround match in serbia on indoor clay in march  isner described the selection as a dream come true isner next entered the  regions morgan keegan championships in memphis seeded sixth he made it to the finals before losing to sam querrey in the doubles event isner teamed up with querrey to win the tournament defeating britishaustralian pair of ross hutchins and jordan kerr prior to the davis cup tie isner competed at the  abierto mexicano telcel championships an atp world tour  series event on clay where he was the fifth seed he lost in the first round to simon greul despite the loss isner following the tournament moved into the top  for the first time isner appeared at the  davis cup first round where usa was up against serbia in his two singles matches he faced serbias team of world no  novak djokovic and world no  viktor troicki he lost the first singles match against viktor troicki but bounced back by winning the doubles match with bob bryan as a replacement for foodpoisoned mike bryan in his second singles match he lost to novak djokovic which enabled serbia to defeat the united states at the  bnp paribas open masters  in indian wells he was seeded th and advanced to the fourth round before losing to world no  and defending champion rafael nadal afterwards he appeared in the second master series tournament of the season the  sony ericsson open masters  in miami as the th seed he advanced to the third round before losing to th seed juan carlos ferrero isner began the claycourt season with an openinground loss to world no  xavier malisse at the us mens claycourt championship followed by a round of  showing at his firstever rome masters where he defeated horacio zeballos before losing to thomaz bellucci however he teamed with querrey to reach the doubles final in rome before losing to bob and mike bryan his doubles performance raised his doubles ranking to the top  for the first time his next tournament was the  serbian open where he was the second seed behind defending champion tournament host and world no  djokovic isner advanced to the first claycourt final of his career third final of the year and fourth final of his career in the final he lost to querrey despite having a match point this was the second consecutive final isner lost to querrey after serving for the championship however isners finals performance improved his ranking to a careerhigh no  isners next tournament was his debut appearance at the madrid masters seeded thirteenth he advanced to the round of  before losing to world no  and eventual champion nadal isner then played in the  french open his ranking assured his first direct seed into a grand slam event seeded th he defeated andrey golubev in the first round for his first singles victory at the french open he advanced to the third round before losing to no  seed and eventual semifinalist tomáš berdych in doubles he and querrey were the th seeds but withdrew prior to the start of the tournament after querreys firstround loss in singles despite being ranked no  in the world entering the wimbledon isner was seeded th by the tournament committee due to his lack of experience on grass but was moved up to rd following the withdrawal of radek štěpánek in the first round isner played nicolas mahut in the longest match in tennis history prevailing – – – – – however fatigued and having little time to recover his energy isner was beaten by thiemo de bakker in the second round – – – having served no aces he also pulled out of the doubles where he and querrey had been th seeds despite having been eliminated in the second round isners total of  aces were more than any other player throughout the championship his wimbledon performance brought his ranking to a careerhigh no  in the world isners next tournament was the  atlanta tennis championships where he played doubles with james blake and reached the semifinals in singles isner was second seed and made it to his fourth final of the year before losing to mardy fish which dropped his career record in finals to – – against americans isner next competed at the legg mason tennis classic the atp world tour  series event in washington dc and site of his breakthrough performance in  isner was also to compete in the doubles with sam querrey but withdrew due to shoulder concerns seeded fifth in singles isner made it to the round of  before losing to xavier malisse isner next played in the cincinnati masters where he was unseeded after defeating łukasz kubot in the first round he faced  wimbledon finalist and  tennis masters cup champion david nalbandian but was forced to retire up a break at – in the first set after injuring his right ankle although isner was found to have suffered ligament damage to the ankle he chose not to withdraw from the us open singles tournament at the  us open isner was th seed and defeated frederico gil in the first round after the match he revealed that although the initial diagnosis was a right ankle ligament tear a second opinion revealed that the damage was a strain and not a tear and he declared his ankle  healed he then advanced to the third round before losing to th seed and  us open semifinalist mikhail youzhny the loss dropped isner out of the top  and from the no  to the no  ranked american player due to his ankle injury he chose not to compete in doubles following the us open isner participated with mardy fish and sam querrey in the davis cup tie against colombia winning the doubles match with fish as his partner the us won the match – to remain in the  davis cup world group isner was next granted a wildcard to participate in the  china open his first time competing in beijing in doubles he teamed with querrey losing in the first round to bob and mike bryan in singles isner was unseeded but made it to the semifinals before losing to world no  and defending champion novak djokovic isner next competed in the shanghai masters where he was unseeded and made it to the second round before losing to world no  and reigning australian open champion roger federer in their first meeting since the  us open  second and third atp titlesedit isner began the year by teaming with bethanie matteksands to win the mixed doubles hopman cup final for the us defeating belgiums justine henin and ruben bemelmans following his win in perth isner returned to auckland to defend his atp title at the  heineken open after a bye in his first round the third seed faced dutch world no  robin haase isner defeated haase to go through to the quarterfinals where he was defeated by david nalbandian in straight sets isner next played in the  australian open he entered the tournament seeded th and received a tough draw including radek štěpánek marin čilić and rafael nadal isner came up against french world no  florent serra whom he easily defeated isner faced radek štěpánek in the second round after losing the first set isner rallied to defeat stepanek to progress into the third round in the third round isner faced fellow top player marin čilić the match went to five sets with cilic emerging as the eventual winner at the  french open isner was drawn against top seed and defending champion rafael nadal isner